{
    "title": "Account Director",
    "skills": "Sales and Business Development",
    "Industry": "Transportation, Logistics, Supply Chain and Storage",
    "seniority": "Not Applicable",
    "baseSalary": {
        "maxValue": "350000.00",
        "minValue": "250000.00",
        "unitText": "YEAR"
    },
    "description": "Cloudinary was founded in 2012 to solve a simple problem: making it an easy platform to manage images &amp; videos. Over the years we evolved into a $120 million+ annual recurring revenue business serving 10,000 companies across industries – from the smallest Shopify stores to iconic brands like Nike and other worldwide companies.  Cloudinary is now the foundational technology for all images and videos on the internet. Only we provide robust, flexible, and intelligent solutions for every business in the world to harness the power of visual media to tell its story. As a single source of truth for brands’ image and video needs, we also provide a comprehensive array of APIs and integrations to transform every brand into a masterful visual storyteller.  If images and video are the electricity powering the new digital world, Cloudinary is the power grid: enabling anyone to easily plug in and “light up” their business with high-impact visual media, without worrying about the science behind the electrical current.  We seek a driven and passionate Account Director to join our team to drive growth and retention in the North Americas regions for our most strategic accounts. As a Cloudinary Account Director, you will be responsible for nurturing and retaining top existing client relationships and identifying and closing new growth opportunities across Cloudinary’s full suite of products. Prior experience managing strategic accounts and selling Saas in the enterprise space is required. This person must be a self-starter who can create a large business pipeline and help customers achieve their goals.  Why Join Cloudinary:  Opportunity to work with cutting-edge technology and industry-leading clients.  A collaborative and inclusive work culture that values creativity, innovation, and diversity.  Competitive compensation package with performance-based incentives.  Flexible remote work options and opportunities for career advancement and professional development.  If you are passionate about helping clients succeed in the digital world and thrive in a fast-paced, innovative environment, we want to hear from you!  Responsibilities:  Identify and close upsell and cross-sell opportunities to maximize revenue from top existing accountsDevelop and maintain strong relationships with key stakeholders within client organizationsCreate, develop, and execute strategic territory and account plansUnderstand clients' business objectives and challenges to effectively position Cloudinary's solutionsCollaborate with cross-functional teams, including Sales, Customer Success, and Product, to deliver exceptional service and support to clientsAct as a trusted advisor to clients, providing guidance on best practices for media management and optimizationMonitor client usage and performance metrics to identify areas for improvement and optimizationMaintain accurate and current account and opportunity forecasting within internal sales toolsStay updated on industry trends, competitive landscape, and emerging technologies to better serve clientsEnsure customer satisfaction and retention    About You:  10+ years of experience in a quota-carrying role Proven history of over-achievement and meeting targets in account management and sales roles within the SaaS industryStrong understanding of cloud-based technologies and servicesExcellent communication and interpersonal skills, with the ability to effectively present technical information to both technical and non-technical audiencesAbility to work independently and as part of a team in a fast-paced environmentWillingness to travel for client meetings and industry events    Cloudinary is proud to be an equal opportunity employer dedicated to pursuing a diverse workforce.  \"We are dedicated to fostering an environment of transparency and equity in our hiring practices. In alignment with these values, we are pleased to provide a salary range for our positions based in the United States of America. The OTE range for this role is based on the location where you reside. We firmly believe that every candidate's skills, experience, and contributions are valuable, and it's our commitment to compensate accordingly. By sharing this information upfront, we aim to ensure that all candidates understand the base salary numbers associated with this position from the outset. We encourage open dialogue and transparency throughout the hiring process, and we are eager to discuss further during the interview stages. We aim to build a team where each member feels valued and fairly compensated for their contributions. Thank you for considering joining our team, and we look forward to the possibility of working together.\"              Show more                Show less",
    "employmentType": "Full-time"
}

{
    "@type": "JobPosting",
    "image": "https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/D4E0BAQHO-rJKhuByHg/company-logo_100_100/company-logo_100_100/0/1719591197696/cloudinary_logo?e=2147483647&v=beta&t=S0m8nZCq-I33eC4WN8akFsq2qyQ8s2H6B2VI1R64eVk",
    "title": "Lead Software Engineer - Moderation - AI",
    "skills": "",
    "@context": "http://schema.org",
    "industry": "Transportation, Logistics, Supply Chain and Storage",
    "datePosted": "2025-01-23T13:18:07.000Z",
    "identifier": {
        "name": "Cloudinary",
        "@type": "PropertyValue",
        "value": "5629a464-3c10-42e7-ac76-8f24453e63bc"
    },
    "description": "We are here to build Cloudinary’s next big thing. We accelerate Cloudinary’s business growth by quickly developing & validating new product ideas in search of product-market fit. The potential impact is huge, we have a lot on our plate, and we could use some help around here.  Cloudinary is seeking an R&D Lead to lead the development of Moderation, a new product being built in its Emerging Business group. Moderation will leverage visual media AI to perform brand-aligned moderation of images and videos. We’re a small-sized, high-paced, and incredibly independent team. We take full end-to-end ownership of our product - from design and development to deployment and testing.   Responsibilities     Take a hands-on role in all development efforts, operating as both a leader and an individual contributor, like a Co-founder & CTO  Co-lead the pod alongside its GM as a counterpart  Develop deep understanding of the target user persona’s needs, and passion for the underlying market problem, to build a product that would delight them  Leverage Cloudinary’s powerful platform to get a product to market as soon as possible, only developing what will move the needle  Constantly adjust focus to what is needed to make the product/venture successful       Requirements     10+ years of development experience  3+ years of development manager experience  Proficient in Python and have experience with machine learning/LLM/Gen AI libraries and frameworks  Extensive experience serving large Enterprise customers - a strong advantage  Strong hands-on experience with cloud platforms, preferably AWS  Knowledge of image or video technologies is an advantage  Knowledge of cloud-based architectures and web technologies  Enthusiastic, humble, and user-centric  Eager to learn new things      Cloudinary is a leading cloud-based image and video management platform, and this is an excellent opportunity to join a growing company and be a part of the develop ment and growth of a new, exciting product. The team is initially small and focused on product and R&D, with additional disciplines added as the product gains traction. If you are a highly experienced and motivated individual with a passion for building successful products, we would love to hear from you.  ",
