        "value": "a7e9856d-7916-4935-beaf-9505831fa170"
    },
    "description": "Cloudinary is looking for a Workplace Experience Manager with a passion for people and a desire to help drive culture. This is a great opportunity for you to drive a high-quality employee experience through initiatives and bring out the best in people. Your goal is to enhance the workplace experience with your know-how to develop an environment for increased creativity, productivity, and well-being. You will drive continuous improvement in the operational efficiency and processes across our locations, constantly finding ways to improve our processes while providing exceptional service and effectively managing our costs.   Responsibilities:      Must be physically in the office by no later than 8:30 am Monday, Wednesday, and Thursday, and no later than 7:15 am on Tuesdays. Must be able to stay until at least 5 pm on Thursdays       Office Management     Develop, implement, and maintain office guides and procedures  Oversee the maintenance of office facilities and equipment  Responsible for overseeing day-to-day operations of our office and related workplace programs  Manage office supplies inventory and place orders as necessary  Ensure the office environment is clean, safe, well-organized, and energetic  Manage meal service for the office  Manage mail via our PO box (regular pick-ups)  Organize, select, and/or distribute swag to NA employees  Welcome new folks and visitors to the office and ensure they have everything they need to be comfortable and productive  Partner with IT to oversee the use and maintenance of office technology       Activities and Events     Responsible for planning, executing, and participating in regular events (ie. Happy Hour, volunteer, social activities) both in the office and remote  Lead Employee Events and Activities committee  Meet weekly with the global team to coordinate and plan company-wide events (ie. Fun Day, Health Day, Family & Friends Day))  Work closely with cross-functional leaders to assist with internal and external meetings and events (virtual and onsite)  Assist with travel arrangements as needed       Communication     Act as the primary point of contact for internal and external communications  Proactively communicate weekly updates, and events, to the NA teams  Share applicable communications to broader Cloudinary and external       Project Management     Assist in planning and executing office-related projects and events  Monitor project timelines and deliverables       Financial Duties     Assist in budget preparation and expense management  Handle invoices, and receipts, via Tipalti and Mesh  Liaise with the Finance team to ensure accurate financial record-keeping via Tipalti and Mesh       Compliance and Security     Ensure compliance with health and safety regulations  Maintain confidentiality of sensitive information and documents  Implement and manage office security protocols       About You:      5+ years of owning and creating people experiences in a workplace  Proven skills in planning, budgeting, and project management  Experience with creatively planning and executing employee events  Ability to handle sensitive and/or confidential information  Experience working with building management and landlords, including office refurbishments, maintenance, and other facilities-related projects  Exceptional written and verbal communication skills  Experience with MacBook, Google Suite, MS Office, and Excel      ",
