{
    "title": "Technical Trainer (Contract)",
    "skills": "Information Technology",
    "Industry": "Transportation, Logistics, Supply Chain and Storage",
    "seniority": "Not Applicable",
    "baseSalary": {
        "maxValue": "70.00",
        "minValue": "50.00",
        "unitText": "HOUR"
    },
    "description": "We are seeking an energetic Technical Trainer with strong communication skills to join our team, available as a contractor for 6-9 months. The Technical Trainer will be instrumental in delivering virtual and on-site training sessions for Cloudinary’s customers who are responsible for image and video management efforts in their organizations throughout the world. This role is essential for fulfilling our obligations through new business, supporting growth and expansion in existing accounts, and utilizing a curriculum developed by the Customer Education team, tailored specifically for our customers.  Why Join Us:  This position offers a unique opportunity to play a key role in our growth and expansion efforts. By joining our team, you will contribute to the success of our customers and the overall business, ensuring that our training programs are effective, scalable, and impactful.  If you are passionate about education, technology, and customer success, we invite you to apply and help us achieve our business goals through exceptional training delivery.  Responsibilities:  Subject Matter Expertise: Learn how to proficiently use Cloudinary’s various products and answer questions about their capabilities without having to regularly further consult documentation or other information sourcesTraining Delivery: Conduct comprehensive training sessions for customers on-site or virtually, ensuring they are well-versed in our products, such as Programmable Media and Cloudinary AssetsTeam Collaboration: Work closely with others in Customer Success and other customer-facing departments to learn about our customers’ use cases and challenges with Cloudinary products, to provide meaningful facilitation and instructionCurriculum Adaptation: Utilize and adapt the curriculum developed by the Customer Education team to meet the specific needs of our customersProject Management: Oversee multiple training projects and their associated timelines, resources, and deliverables, ensuring seamless integration with other Customer Success initiatives for the customersPerformance and Impact Assessment: Assist Customer Success leadership in measuring the impact of training sessions in terms of product adoption and usage with actionable feedback to optimize curriculum and instruction for future delivery, as well as Product roadmap development suggestions    About You:  You have proven experience in a technical training role for software products with delivery to a wide range of users with varying levels of product knowledge and technical expertiseYou possess excellent communication, presentation, and facilitation skills in the English language, with the ability to translate complex technical information into engaging and easy-to-understand instructionYou thrive in a fast-paced, collaborative environment and excel at working cross-functionally with various stakeholdersYou have a strong understanding of e-learning platforms and technologies, as well as adult learning methodologies, processes, and best practicesYou are willing to travel to customer locations for training sessions and can navigate cultural differences and tailor sessions to diverse audiences (It is a plus, not required)    \"We are dedicated to fostering an environment of transparency and equity in our hiring practices. In alignment with these values, we are pleased to provide a range for our positions based in the United States of America. The contractor hourly range for this role is based on the location where you reside. We firmly believe that every candidate's skills, experience, and contributions are valuable, and it's our commitment to compensate accordingly. By sharing this information upfront, we aim to ensure that all candidates understand the base salary numbers associated with this position from the outset. We encourage open dialogue and transparency throughout the hiring process, and we are eager to discuss further during the interview stages. We aim to build a team where each member feels valued and fairly compensated for their contributions. Thank you for considering joining our team, and we look forward to the possibility of working together.\"              Show more                Show less",
    "employmentType": "Full-time"
}

