al and onsite)Assist with travel arrangements as needed    Communication  Act as the primary point of contact for internal and external communicationsProactively communicate weekly updates, and events, to the NA teamsShare applicable communications to broader Cloudinary and external    Project Management  Assist in planning and executing office-related projects and eventsMonitor project timelines and deliverables    Financial Duties  Assist in budget preparation and expense managementHandle invoices, and receipts, via Tipalti and MeshLiaise with the Finance team to ensure accurate financial record-keeping via Tipalti and Mesh    Compliance and Security  Ensure compliance with health and safety regulationsMaintain confidentiality of sensitive information and documentsImplement and manage office security protocols    New Employee Orientation  Deliver a high-quality onboarding experience that helps new employees feel welcome and connected from their first day    About You:  5+ years of owning and creating people experiences in a workplaceProven skills in planning, budgeting, and project managementExperience with creatively planning and executing employee eventsAbility to handle sensitive and/or confidential informationExperience working with building management and landlords, including office refurbishments, maintenance, and other facilities-related projectsExceptional written and verbal communication skillsExperience with MacBook, Google Suite, MS Office, and Excel    \"We are dedicated to fostering an environment of transparency and equity in our hiring practices. In alignment with these values, we are pleased to provide a salary range for our positions based in the United States of America. The salary range for this role is based on the location where you reside. We firmly believe that every candidate's skills, experience, and contributions are valuable, and it's our commitment to compensate accordingly. By sharing this information upfront, we aim to ensure that all