    "description": "Cloudinary is looking for a People Experience Manager with a passion for people and a desire to help drive culture. This is a great opportunity for you to drive a high-quality employee experience through initiatives and bring out the best in people. Your goal is to enhance the workplace experience with your know-how to develop an environment for increased creativity, productivity, and well-being. You will drive continuous improvement in the operational efficiency and processes across our locations, constantly finding ways to improve our processes while providing exceptional service and effectively managing our costs.   Responsibilities:      Must be physically in the office by no later than 8:30 am Monday, Wednesday, and Thursday, and no later than 7:15 am on Tuesdays. Must be able to stay until at least 5 pm on Thursdays       Office Management     Develop, implement, and maintain office guides and procedures  Oversee the maintenance of office facilities and equipment  Responsible for overseeing day-to-day operations of our office and related workplace programs  Manage office supplies inventory and place orders as necessary  Ensure the office environment is clean, safe, well-organized, and energetic  Manage meal service for the office  Manage mail via our PO box (regular pick-ups)  Organize, select, and/or distribute swag to NA employees  Welcome new folks and visitors to the office and ensure they have everything they need to be comfortable and productive  Partner with IT to oversee the use and maintenance of office technology       Activities and Events     Responsible for planning, executing, and participating in regular events (ie. Happy Hour, volunteer, social activities) both in the office and remote  Lead Employee Events and Activities committee  Meet weekly with the global team to coordinate and plan company-wide events (ie. Fun Day, Health Day, Family & Friends Day))  Work closely with cross-functional leaders to assist with internal and external meetings and events (virtual and onsite)  Assist with travel arrangements as needed       Communication     Act as the primary point of contact for internal and external communications  Proactively communicate weekly updates, and events, to the NA teams  Share applicable communications to broader Cloudinary and external       Project Management     Assist in planning and executing office-related projects and events  Monitor project timelines and deliverables       Financial Duties     Assist in budget preparation and expense management  Handle invoices, and receipts, via Tipalti and Mesh  Liaise with the Finance team to ensure accurate financial record-keeping via Tipalti and Mesh       Compliance and Security     Ensure compliance with health and safety regulations  Maintain confidentiality of sensitive information and documents  Implement and manage office security protocols       New Employee Orientation     Deliver a high-quality onboarding experience that helps new employees feel welcome and connected from their first day       About You:      5+ years of owning and creating people experiences in a workplace  Proven skills in planning, budgeting, and project management  Experience with creatively planning and executing employee events  Ability to handle sensitive and/or confidential information  Experience working with building management and landlords, including office refurbishments, maintenance, and other facilities-related projects  Exceptional written and verbal communication skills  Experience with MacBook, Google Suite, MS Office, and Excel      \"We are dedicated to fostering an environment of transparency and equity in our hiring practices. In alignment with these values, we are pleased to provide a salary range for our positions based in the United States of America. The salary range for this role is based on the location where you reside. We firmly believe that every candidate's skills, experience, and contributions are valuable, and it's our commitment to compensate accordingly. By sharing this information upfront, we aim to ensure that all candidates understand the base salary numbers associated with this position from the outset. We encourage open dialogue and transparency throughout the hiring process, and we are eager to discuss further during the interview stages. We aim to build a team where each member feels valued and fairly compensated for their contributions. Thank you for considering joining our team, and we look forward to the possibility of working together.\"  ",
