    },
    "description": "We are seeking a driven and passionate Strategic Account Manager to join our team to drive growth and retention for our strategic accounts. As a Cloudinary Account Manager, you will be responsible for nurturing and retaining existing client relationships and identifying and closing new growth opportunities across Cloudinary’s full suite of products. Prior experience managing strategic accounts and selling Saas in the enterprise space is required. This person must be a self-starter who can create a large business pipeline and help customers achieve their goals.   Responsibilities:     Identify and close upsell and cross-sell opportunities to maximize revenue from existing accounts  Develop and maintain strong relationships with key stakeholders within client organizations  Create, develop, and execute strategic territory and account plans  Understand clients' business objectives and challenges to position Cloudinary's solutions effectively  Collaborate with cross-functional teams, including Sales, Customer Success, and Product, to deliver exceptional service and support to clients  Act as a trusted advisor to clients, providing guidance on best practices for media management and optimization  Monitor client usage and performance metrics to identify areas for improvement and optimization  Maintain accurate and current account and opportunity forecasting within internal sales tools  Stay updated on industry trends, competitive landscape, and emerging technologies to better serve clients  Ensure customer satisfaction and retention       About you:     5+ years of experience in a quota-carrying role   Proven history of over-achievement and meeting targets in account management and sales roles within the SaaS industry  Strong understanding of cloud-based technologies and services  Excellent communication and interpersonal skills, with the ability to effectively present technical information to both technical and non-technical audiences  Ability to work independently and as part of a team in a fast-paced environment  Willingness to travel for client meetings and industry events      ",
