    },
    "description": "Cloudinary is looking for a Product Marketing Director to join our team to drive the success of our API-first Video product line. This individual will lead key product efforts and is expected to bring innovative ideas and creative strategies to accelerate Cloudinary’s growth in the industry. You, as the expert, will collaborate with cross-functional teams to generate market awareness and revenue for our Video Platform and Video APIs. Come join us here at Cloudinary.   Responsibilities:      Lead product marketing for the Cloudinary Video product line  Position Cloudinary as a clearly differentiated Video vendor to customers, prospects, analysts  Bring deep industry insights and subject expertise in the Video space to the product and marketing teams  Craft compelling product messaging and stories for key use cases, industries, personas, and market segments   Work with the corporate marketing, demand gen, CSM, and growth teams to drive awareness, campaigns, opportunities, and upsell/cross-sell for Video with prospects and current customers  Create value-based content and sales enablement in the form of presentations, web content, blogs, datasheets, brochures, customer case studies, demos, videos, and training materials  Launch new innovations to market  Advise product roadmap in close partnership with product management and product strategy teams  Represent Cloudinary at thought leadership, demand generation, and company events as a Video SME  Advise self-serve teams on strategies for positioning, messaging, and packaging/pricing to optimize Video PLG motion   Analyze the market and key competitors to articulate differentiators  Work with the PR and AR teams to brief media and analysts  Drive win/loss analysis for Video to understand why we win or lose       About You:     10+ years of product marketing experience (can include product management experience)   3+ years experience in the video space preferred   Must have experience with SaaS  Excellent writing and presentation skills  Experience with multiple business buyer personas, including technical buyers  Proven creativity and messaging skills  Highly analytical, data-driven approach  Comfortable with both high-level strategy and hands-on work      ",
