        "value": "5629a464-3c10-42e7-ac76-8f24453e63bc"
    },
    "description": "We are here to build Cloudinary’s next big thing. We accelerate Cloudinary’s business growth by quickly developing & validating new product ideas in search of product-market fit. The potential impact is huge, we have a lot on our plate, and we could use some help around here.  Cloudinary is seeking an R&D Lead to lead the development of Moderation, a new product being built in its Emerging Business group. Moderation will leverage visual media AI to perform brand-aligned moderation of images and videos. We’re a small-sized, high-paced, and incredibly independent team. We take full end-to-end ownership of our product - from design and development to deployment and testing.   Responsibilities     Take a hands-on role in all development efforts, operating as both a leader and an individual contributor, like a Co-founder & CTO  Co-lead the venture alongside its GM as a counterpart  Develop deep understanding of the target user persona’s needs, and passion for the underlying market problem, to build a product that would delight them  Leverage Cloudinary’s powerful platform to get a product to market as soon as possible, only developing what will move the needle  Constantly adjust focus to what is needed to make the product/venture successful       Requirements     10+ years of development experience  3+ years of development manager experience  Proficient in Python and have experience with machine learning/LLM/Gen AI libraries and frameworks  Extensive experience serving large Enterprise customers - a strong advantage  Strong hands-on experience with cloud platforms, preferably AWS  Knowledge of image or video technologies is an advantage  Knowledge of cloud-based architectures and web technologies  Enthusiastic, humble, and user-centric  Eager to learn new things      Cloudinary is a leading cloud-based image and video management platform, and this is an excellent opportunity to join a growing company and be a part of the develop ment and growth of a new, exciting product. The team is initially small and focused on product and R&D, with additional disciplines added as the product gains traction. If you are a highly experienced and motivated individual with a passion for building successful products, we would love to hear from you.  ",
