    "description": "We are here to build Cloudinary’s next big thing. We accelerate Cloudinary’s business growth by quickly developing & validating new product ideas in search of product-market fit. The potential impact is huge, we have a lot on our plate, and we could use some help around here.  Cloudinary is seeking a senior developer to help develop Moderation, a new product being built in its Emerging Business group. Moderation will leverage visual media AI to perform brand-aligned moderation of images and videos. We’re a small-sized, high-paced, and incredibly independent team. We take full end-to-end ownership of our product - from design and development to deployment and testing.   Responsibilities     Develop deep understanding of the target user persona’s needs, and build a product that would delight them  Leverage Cloudinary’s powerful platform to get a product to market as soon as possible, only developing what will move the needle  Constantly adjust focus to what is needed to make the product/venture successful       Requirements     5+ years of professional experience as a full-stack developer  Proficient in Python and have experience with machine learning/LLM/Gen AI libraries and frameworks  Strong hands-on experience with cloud platforms, preferably AWS  Knowledge of cloud-based architectures and web technologies  Knowledge of image or video technologies is an advantage  Enthusiastic, humble, and user-centric  Eager to learn new things  Prior experience in a startup environment is an advantage, ideally as a founding team member      Cloudinary is a leading cloud-based image and video management platform, and this is an excellent opportunity to join a growing company and be a part of the development and growth of a new, exciting product. The team is initially small and focused on product and R&D, with additional disciplines added as the product gains traction. If you are a highly experienced and motivated individual with a passion for building successful products, we would love to hear from you.  ",
