    "description": "We're looking for a Senior Information Systems Engineer to lead the design, integration, and automation of our enterprise IT systems.  This role is ideal for someone who thrives on building smart, secure, and scalable business solutions across platforms like Salesforce, NetSuite, Zendesk, and Marketo.  You’ll own end-to-end execution of system automations, process improvements, and technical integrations—bringing together the needs of GTM, Finance, CS, and Security teams.  You’ll work hands-on with tools like Okta, Google Workspace, Jamf, and no/low-code platforms (Zapier, Workato, Tray.io) to drive efficiency, security, and business alignment.   What You’ll Do     Build and maintain secure, scalable integrations across core business systems  Translate business needs into system workflows and automations  Lead automation initiatives using scripting and no/low-code tools  Ensure compliance and security best practices (SOC2, ISO 27001, GDPR)  Collaborate with cross-functional teams to support business growth  Evaluate emerging tech like AI to improve IT operations       What You Bring     Proven experience with IT systems, SaaS tools, and enterprise integrations  Strong scripting or automation background (Python, JS, PowerShell, Bash)  Deep understanding of IAM, API security, and compliance frameworks  Experience working with business stakeholders and system architects  A strategic mindset with hands-on execution skills  Bonus Points For  Experience with data pipelines or analytics platforms  Familiarity with ITIL and governance best practices    ",
