    "description": " Job Description    Your mission at IntegriChain:   The Gross to Net (GTN) Senior Analyst is a key member of IntegriChain’s SaaS and BPaaS Organization, which provides managed services and business process outsourcing in support of bio-pharmaceutical clients.   What This Role Entails     Drive Customer GTN Close and Forecast processes      Prepare monthly revenue related journal entries and ledger account reconciliations leveraging both excel models and an automated GTN software suite  Perform true-ups based on actual versus accrued contra revenue GTN deduction items  Conduct reconciliations of actual transaction data to the associated accrual assumptions  Analyze, explain, and meaningfully summarize gross to net variances to customers  Alert customers to potential changes that may affect their business  Support the growth of the GTN Managed Services department  Participate in developmental opportunities and training  Track, maintain, and report monthly and quarterly operation metrics to direct supervisor  Continuously communicate with customer points of contact  Comply with internal policies/procedures to ensure SOC1 compliance and customer SLAs are met  Support new analysts during the onboarding period. This includes department specific training, customer training, systems training, and department workflow  Create reusable department templates & training/reference materials  Drive customer success  Create on-time, high quality project deliverables while managing expectations internally and externally  Execute, analyze, and maintain GTN data and calculations within the GTN software suite  Perform ongoing maintenance processes and communicate deficiencies through reporting mechanisms  Perform analysis and troubleshooting for customers  Anticipate and meet shifting customer needs, proactively elevating issues as required  Value and build relationships with customer IT, operations, and finance staff  Collaborate cross-functionally  Work closely with the GTN Advisory team to provide critical analysis of GTN-related data sets, and triage customer issues and reconciliation variances  Assist cross-functional business teams to meet goals of shared service arrangements  Attend customer, department, and company meetings  ",
