    "description": " Company Description   IntegriChain is the data and application backbone for market access departments of Life Sciences manufacturers. We deliver the data, the applications, and the business process infrastructure for patient access and therapy commercialization. More than 250 manufacturers rely on our ICyte Platform to orchestrate their commercial and government payer contracting, patient services, and distribution channels. ICyte is the first and only platform that unites the financial, operational, and commercial data sets required to support therapy access in the era of specialty and precision medicine. With ICyte, Life Sciences innovators can digitalize their market access operations, freeing up resources to focus on more data-driven decision support as well as labor-intensive processes – allowing their best talent to identify and resolve coverage and availability hurdles and to manage pricing and forecasting complexity.  We are headquartered in Philadelphia, PA (USA) with offices in Ambler, PA (USA); Raleigh, NC (USA); Pune, India; and Medellín, Colombia. For more information, visit www.integrichain.com, or follow us on Twitter @IntegriChain and LinkedIn.   Job Description   IntegriChain is seeking a polished, detail-oriented, India-based professional to provide ongoing customer support to the most innovative life sciences and pharmaceutical companies in the world.  This role, within the SaaS & BPaaS practice at IntegriChain, is part of an elite team who leverage their Life Sciences domain expertise to analyze, model, and synthesize information to provide compliance insights to our State Price Transparency Reporting (SPTR) customers. The analyst will work alongside our US and Pune based teams of seasoned industry experts to provide prompt, accurate, and compliant support to our customers.  In order to be successful the analyst will need to excel in a fast paced environment in order to provide required deliverables to customers as well as be growth oriented to transition into the main communication lead on customer accounts. This individual will be responsible for maintaining compliance for the accounts they oversee and need to be able to manage the end to end project workflow across multiple customers at the same time.  The position requires refined critical thinking skills: aggressively seeking information and answers, managing expectations while meeting commitments, always delivering work of utmost quality, on time, and communicating effectively throughout. This candidate has a naturally inquisitive mindset, a desire to quickly learn the complexities of the pharmaceutical landscape as well as the ability to demonstrate high-level analytical and strategic thinking.   Responsibilities:     Support projects and customer engagements where IntegriChain is providing ongoing strategic, operational and compliance SPTR support  Provide strategic guidance and operational support related to State Price Transparency reporting obligations including the preparation of reports  Create deliverables of utmost quality for customers, manage timelines internally and externally, and provide on or ahead of time delivery to ensure customer account satisfaction in order to encourage referrals, drive incremental revenue opportunities, and ensure renewal business on existing accounts  Manage multiple projects and responsibilities in parallel, while ensuring timely delivery and responses to customer requests  Work within a rapidly growing organization where cross-functional communication is important and a willingness to evolve and adapt to changing organization needs and challenges is imperative  Understand the overall organization structure and interplay of the various segments within IntegriChain  Generate and review all pricing reporting data necessary to ensure compliance with all statutory state reporting requirements.   Align with customers to ensure all data gathered for reports is reviewed, approved, documented, and submitted in compliance with each state obligation  Effectively communicate between internal/external client stakeholders  Stay abreast of trends and regulations to ensure effectiveness and compliance     Qualifications   Minimum Requirements:    Minimum B.A. / B.S.   Life Sciences industry experience suggested  Strong interpersonal skills and understanding of cross-functional team work  Proficient in Excel and PowerPoint with excellent presentation skills  Excellent business analytical skills, a high accuracy rate, and attention to detail  Demonstrate problem solving and decision-making skills with the ability to “think on their feet” and suggest alternatives and solutions  Ability to work independently as well as in a team setting    Preferred Requirements:    Proficient in Google Suite - Gmail, Docs, Sheets, Slides    Additional Information   What does IntegriChain have to offer?     Mission driven: Work with the purpose of helping to improve patients' lives!   Excellent and affordable medical benefits + non-medical perks including Flexible Paid Time Off (PTO) and much more!  Robust Learning & Development opportunities including over 700+ development courses free to all employees    IntegriChain is committed to equal treatment and opportunity in all aspects of recruitment, selection, and employment without regard to race, color, religion, national origin, ethnicity, age, sex, marital status, physical or mental disability, gender identity, sexual orientation, veteran or military status, or any other category protected under the law. IntegriChain is an equal opportunity employer; committed to creating a community of inclusion, and an environment free from discrimination, harassment, and retaliation.  ",
