        "value": "744000009679190"
    },
    "description": " Company Description   IntegriChain offers the leading technology platform for pharmaceutical commercialization and market access. We are dedicated to providing the life sciences industry with innovative software, robust data solutions, and expert advisory services. Our goal is to optimize market access, enhance revenue generation and insight, and streamline supply chains, ensuring that patients receive the therapy they need while helping manufacturers achieve their business goals and improve outcomes.  We are headquartered in Philadelphia, PA (USA), with offices in: Ambler, PA (USA); Pune, India; and Medellín, Colombia. For more information, visit www.integrichain.com, or follow us on Twitter @IntegriChain and LinkedIn.   Job Description    Position Overview   We are looking for a visionary and strategic leader to join our team as the Vice President, Financial Planning & Analysis (FP&A). In this critical role, reporting directly to the CFO, you will shape the future of our finance function and drive IntegriChain's overall performance. This is an exceptional opportunity for a strategic thinker who excels at transforming complex data into actionable insights and guiding our growth and success.   Key Responsibilities     Lead the annual planning process, along with monthly and quarterly forecasting and long-range planning.   Develop and implement a robust Key Performance Indicator (KPI) framework that aligns financial metrics with strategic decision-making.   Collaborate with cross-functional teams to gather, analyze, and convert data into actionable insights and strategic recommendations.   Analyze market trends, competitive landscapes, and industry benchmarks to inform financial strategies.   Provide strategic, financial guidance to leadership, enabling informed decision-making.   Identify opportunities for investment in growth and develop corresponding commercial targets.   Ensure effective communication of financial insights and reports to various stakeholders.   Manage and mentor a high-performing FP&A team, fostering a culture of continuous improvement and professional development.   Enhance system alignment to improve the performance of both the finance organization and the broader business.   Drive operational efficiency and excellence across the organization.   Evaluate M&A targets and potential synergies to support underwriting and value creation plans.      Qualifications    What you will bring to the table:      8-10 years of progressive finance experience, with a strong emphasis on FP&A.   Experienced in financial modeling, forecasting, and budgeting  Possess strong analytical and strategic thinking skills, enabling you to easily translate complex financial data into actionable insights  Excellent communication and presentation skills, with the ability to articulate financial concepts to both technical and non-technical audiences     Additional Information  Join IntegriChain and be a part of a dynamic team that is revolutionizing the pharmaceutical industry. We offer a collaborative and innovative work environment, competitive compensation and opportunities for professional growth and development.  If you are ready to elevate your career and make a meaningful impact, we want to hear from you! Apply now to become a key driver of the success as Vice President, FP&A at IntegriChain.   What does IntegriChain have to offer?     Mission driven: Work with the purpose of helping to improve patients' lives!   Excellent and affordable medical benefits + non-medical perks including Flexible Paid Time Off and much more!  Robust Learning & Development opportunities including over 700+ development courses free to all employees    IntegriChain is committed to equal treatment and opportunity in all aspects of recruitment, selection, and employment without regard to race, color, religion, national origin, ethnicity, age, sex, marital status, physical or mental disability, gender identity, sexual orientation, veteran or military status, or any other category protected under the law. IntegriChain is an equal opportunity employer; committed to creating a community of inclusion, and an environment free from discrimination, harassment, and retaliation.    Our policy on visa sponsorship for US based positions:   Applicants for employment in the US must have valid work authorization that does not now and/or will not in the future require sponsorship of a visa for employment authorization in the US by IntegriChain.  ",
