    "description": " Company Description   IntegriChain is the data and application backbone for market access departments of Life Sciences manufacturers. We deliver the data, the applications, and the business process infrastructure for patient access and therapy commercialization. More than 250 manufacturers rely on our ICyte Platform to orchestrate their commercial and government payer contracting, patient services, and distribution channels. ICyte is the first and only platform that unites the financial, operational, and commercial data sets required to support therapy access in the era of specialty and precision medicine. With ICyte, Life Sciences innovators can digitalize their market access operations, freeing up resources to focus on more data-driven decision support as well as labor-intensive processes – allowing their best talent to identify and resolve coverage and availability hurdles and to manage pricing and forecasting complexity.  We are headquartered in Philadelphia, PA (USA) with offices in Ambler, PA (USA); Raleigh, NC (USA); Pune, India; and Medellín, Colombia. For more information, visit www.integrichain.com, or follow us on Twitter @IntegriChain and LinkedIn.   Job Description    Position Details     This role utilizes various systems to support multiple external clients by creating financial reports and analyses (in our support system and Excel). The ability to highlight and explain variances is key to this role, as is rapidly identifying and correcting calculation errors or system issues  Successful candidate will initiate, develop, and manage professional relationships with key internal colleagues  The Analyst will complete a multitude of tasks within the organization and be responsible for collaborating with colleagues in remote locations of varying positions     Job Profile      Gather transactional data, reconcile data to General Ledger, load data to source system  Resolve errors in the GTN system based on defined set of rules and perform correction where required  Generate deliverables based off system results  Meeting contractual deadlines (SLAs), effectively managing workload to accommodate challenging timelines  Review and revise process documentation and ensure it is up to date, create necessary including work instructions and align with RACI policy.   Relies on instructions and pre-established guidelines to perform the functions of the job  Monitors and reviews data output from the system for consistency and formatting     Qualifications     Meeting contractual deadlines (SLAs), effectively managing workload to accommodate challenging timelines  Review and revise process documentation and ensure it is up to date, create necessary including work instructions and align with RACI policy.   Relies on instructions and pre-established guidelines to perform the functions of the job  Monitors and reviews data output from the system for consistency and formatting  Strong analytical and problem-solving skills, with the ability to work with large datasets and complex financial models  Rapidly learn new software and be able to analyze large volumes of data  Strong communication and interpersonal skills to effectively collaborate with cross-functional teams  Excellent attention to detail and accuracy in data analysis and reporting  Process oriented individual with strong organizational and planning skills required to coordinate with external clients  Ability to work with a remote management team on multiple clients in an office environment  Prerequisite   Bachelor's degree from a recognized college or university (information management, finance, accounting, or other business discipline required)  Experience in the pharmaceutical or healthcare industry is desirable  Working knowledge of Managed care, Medicaid, GPO Contracting, or Government Pricing is preferred  Experience with financial report generation, a working knowledge of MS-Office and Excel is must  Preferred familiarity with GTN calculations and revenue recognition in the pharmaceutical industry    Additional Information   What does IntegriChain have to offer?     Mission driven: Work with the purpose of helping to improve patients' lives!   Excellent and affordable medical benefits + non-medical perks including Flexible Paid Time Off (PTO) and much more!  Robust Learning & Development opportunities including over 700+ development courses free to all employees    IntegriChain is committed to equal treatment and opportunity in all aspects of recruitment, selection, and employment without regard to race, color, religion, national origin, ethnicity, age, sex, marital status, physical or mental disability, gender identity, sexual orientation, veteran or military status, or any other category protected under the law. IntegriChain is an equal opportunity employer; committed to creating a community of inclusion, and an environment free from discrimination, harassment, and retaliation.  ",
