        "@type": "PropertyValue",
        "value": "744000002812475"
    },
    "description": " Company Description   IntegriChain is the data and application backbone for market access departments of Life Sciences manufacturers. We deliver the data, the applications, and the business process infrastructure for patient access and therapy commercialization. More than 250 manufacturers rely on our ICyte Platform to orchestrate their commercial and government payer contracting, patient services, and distribution channels. ICyte is the first and only platform that unites the financial, operational, and commercial data sets required to support therapy access in the era of specialty and precision medicine. With ICyte, Life Sciences innovators can digitalize their market access operations, freeing up resources to focus on more data-driven decision support. With ICyte, Life Sciences innovators are digitalizing labor-intensive processes – freeing up their best talent to identify and resolve coverage and availability hurdles and to manage pricing and forecasting complexity.  We are headquartered in Philadelphia, PA (USA), with offices in: Ambler, PA (USA); Pune, India; and Medellín, Colombia. For more information, visit www.integrichain.com, or follow us on Twitter @IntegriChain and LinkedIn.  We are excited to offer a hybrid working environment for our employees. To be successful in this role, there are some requirements to visit our office locations from quarterly to a few times a quarter for workshops, team meetings and collaboration between teams. There may be potential for international travel annually or as needed based on business needs.   Job Description    What this role entails:      Own the calendar and travel schedule for CEO and key Executive Leadership Team (ELT) members  Work with Sales team members to maximize customer travel opportunities through key geographic areas  Handle travel logistics for local and international travel including preparation of itineraries, visas, etc. together with the management of out-of-office requirements  Coordinate key internal meetings (as well as for various ELT members) on items such as catering, meeting space, and group ELT events and dinners  Assist Marketing team with event logistics for major conferences and events  Assist CEO in creating opportunities for and maintaining effective engagement with team members  Assist Portfolio Management Office with strategic planning, event planning & event execution including Quarterly Management Meetings  Develop processes and best practices to support tracking and management of various executive leadership activities, including (but not limited to) compensation and expense approvals, project and program reviews, etc.   Prepare documents and manage spreadsheets in support of key ELT members’ responsibilities and activities  Periodically attend meetings to take minutes or record decisions  This role is primarily onsite in our Philadelphia Office     What success looks like in this role:     Fully organized calendars for assigned members of the Executive Leadership Team, including the CEO, as the primary point of contact for bookings. Understands priorities, and is knowledgeable on meeting topics and meeting participants and uses that information to make scheduling decisions, avoiding overbooking or double-booking.   Anticipates issues, conflicts, and problems and takes proactive action to address them using advanced problem-solving skills   Maintains effective, timely, and positive communication with the ELT and all members of the IntegriChain team as well as external parties, dealing with others with honesty, sincerity, and professionalism  Always maintains a positive attitude and has advanced conflict management skills  Lives our company values of Healthcare Passion, being Data Driven, Proactive, Collaborative, and Accountable     Qualifications    What you’ll need to thrive in this role:     Excellent verbal and written communication skills, with the ability to effectively communicate with individuals at all levels of the organization  Attention to detail, precision and accuracy and flexible mindset  Demonstrated ability to handle confidential and sensitive information with utmost discretion and professionalism  Ability to be in the Center City Philadelphia office 2-3x/week and additionally during any key meeting days   Self-starter who can interact regularly, effectively, and efficiently with the Executive Leadership team as well as with leadership both inside the business and externally  Superior time management skills and attention to detail, as well as the ability to bring structure and organization to ambiguity where needed  Ability to adapt to changing priorities and work effectively in a dynamic and fast-paced environment without supervision, and ability to begin projects independently     What you’ll bring to the table:      A minimum 5+ years as an Assistant to multiple Senior Executives in a Multi-National or Global organization(s)  High level of proficiency in using tools such as Google Suite (preferred) and/or Microsoft Office, calendar management software, instant message and collaboration platforms  A bachelor's degree in Business Administration or a related field is preferred, or equivalent experience  Highly professional demeanor, with the ability to represent the office of the CEO and the organization in a professional manner  Experience in the healthcare and/or pharmaceutical industry a plus    Additional Information   What does IntegriChain have to offer?     Mission driven: Work with the purpose of helping to improve patients' lives!   Excellent and affordable medical benefits + non-medical perks including Flexible Paid Time Off  Robust Learning & Development opportunities including over 700+ development courses free to all employees    IntegriChain is committed to equal treatment and opportunity in all aspects of recruitment, selection, and employment without regard to race, color, religion, national origin, ethnicity, age, sex, marital status, physical or mental disability, gender identity, sexual orientation, veteran or military status, or any other category protected under the law. IntegriChain is an equal opportunity employer; committed to creating a community of inclusion, and an environment free from discrimination, harassment, and retaliation.    Our policy on visa sponsorship for US based positions:   Applicants for employment in the US must have valid work authorization that does not now and/or will not in the future require sponsorship of a visa for employment authorization in the US by IntegriChain.  ",
