lopment, Linux Administration, Network/Data Center Operations, Source Control Management, Database Administration/Migration(NoSQL and SQL)  Contribute to design and strategy conversations  Participate in off hours on-call rotation  Participate in 1st/2nd level on hours support rotations  Enforcing compliance requirements  Manage cloud costs      Individual Outcomes:      Can plan, estimate, commit, and execute on current sprint’s deliverables  Can onboard in 30-60 days from hire date.   Taking to a full complement of points in each sprint  Comfortable soloing off hours on-call rotation  Comfortable with most response plays for on-hours support and delivering within SLA  Willing to enforce Compliance Standards  Willing to enforce Architectural and Operational Standards or production applications  Willing to monitor AWS costs  Willing to hold themselves accountable to our SLAs      Team Outcomes:      Commitment to continuous improvement  Willing to meet SLAs for continuity and uptime  Willing to commit to goals and accept accountability.      Qualifications     Qualifications and Competencies:      Bachelor's Degree in Computer Science or equivalent experience.   1-3 years of Development, Devops, or Data Center Experience  Experience with common GitHub developer practices and paradigms.   Excellent verbal and written communication skills     Requirements     Familiarity with bash and python scripting  Bachelors in CS or related field  Can demonstrate theoretical understanding containerization  Can demonstrate theoretical understanding of common devops concepts(CI/CD, configuration management, principle of least access, etc.)  Practical or classroom experience with AWS      Any of the following are a plus      Docker  Terraform  Linux  Experience with one or more build tools(Jenkins, CircleCI, Travis, etc.)  AWS or Azure Cloud Administration  Bachelors in CS or related field  Java  Ansible  Rundeck  Network Administration    Additional Information   What does IntegriC