    "description": " Job Description   Position Overview  We are looking for a visionary and strategic leader to join our team as the Vice President, Accounting. In this critical role, reporting directly to the CFO, you will provide technical and operational leadership across accounting functions.  Ensure accurate and timely monthly, quarterly, and annual accounting close processes and reporting. Establish internal auditing processes and coordinates external audits. Use in-depth knowledge and understanding of accounting principles and best practices to develop accounting professionals.  Responsible for consolidating internal financial statements by segment and supporting the VP of FP&A with internal and external reporting. Act as a critical partner to the Executive and Senior Management teams. Oversee and manage specific accounting personnel as assigned by the CFO.  Responsible for all cash management functions of the business, including corporate cash, customer cash for rebates, cash flow forecasts and reporting, and interest income. Act as key relationship manager for all lenders; manage all reporting requirements and covenants, including forecasting key metrics.  Oversee compliance activities as assigned by the CFO and assist with special projects as directed by the Executive Leadership Team. Act as a critical point of contact for Merger & Acquisition activity, including incoming and outgoing due diligence requests.  Key Responsibilities  Own monthly, quarterly, and annual corporate financial statement consolidation and reporting, including MD&A for critical stakeholders (Executive Leadership, Investors, and Lenders)  Set and manage key financial calendars and execute periodic financial tasks  Manage the activities and responsibilities of accounting staff, including financial consolidation, the monthly close process, the general ledger, and tax  Responsible for supervision and oversight of audit, financial reporting, quality of close  Support M&A diligence activities and integration  Direct cash management for both corporate cash balances and customer rebate cash  Own and oversee the preparation of the database for incoming due diligence as directed by the CFO  Oversee annual valuation process and own key reporting and updates for equity investors and participants  Support the VP of FP&A with monthly internal reporting and metrics as needed  Own periodic updates for incentive compensation and ensure actual and forecast reserves are sufficient  Prepare and report against monthly cash flow forecasts  Plan and execute all special projects as assigned by the CFO, including analysis of key value drivers of the Company, benchmarking against key competitors, specific customer analyses, and profitability initiatives  Collaborate with CFO and SVP People and Culture regarding office facilities and costs and act as the key point of contact for office leases  Collaborate with SVP People and Culture regarding healthcare and retirement plans and costs  Assess talent effectively and develop managers into promotable talent",
