    "description": " Company Description   IntegriChain is the data and application backbone for market access departments of Life Sciences manufacturers. We deliver the data, the applications, and the business process infrastructure for patient access and therapy commercialization. More than 250 manufacturers rely on our ICyte Platform to orchestrate their commercial and government payer contracting, patient services, and distribution channels. ICyte is the first and only platform that unites the financial, operational, and commercial data sets required to support therapy access in the era of specialty and precision medicine. With ICyte, Life Sciences innovators can digitalize their market access operations, freeing up resources to focus on more data-driven decision support. With ICyte, Life Sciences innovators are digitalizing labor-intensive processes – freeing up their best talent to identify and resolve coverage and availability hurdles and to manage pricing and forecasting complexity.  We are headquartered in Philadelphia, PA (USA), with offices in: Ambler, PA (USA); Pune, India; and Medellín, Colombia. For more information, visit www.integrichain.com, or follow us on Twitter @IntegriChain and LinkedIn.   Job Description    Your mission at IntegriChain:   The Gross to Net (GTN) Senior Analyst is a key member of IntegriChain’s SaaS and BPaaS Organization, which provides managed services and business process outsourcing in support of bio-pharmaceutical clients.   What this role entails:      Drive Customer GTN Close and Forecast processes      Prepare monthly revenue related journal entries and ledger account reconciliations leveraging both excel models and an automated GTN software suite  Perform true-ups based on actual versus accrued contra revenue GTN deduction items  Conduct reconciliations of actual transaction data to the associated accrual assumptions  Analyze, explain, and meaningfully summarize gross to net variances to customers  Alert customers to potential changes that may affect their business  Support the growth of the GTN Managed Services department  Participate in developmental opportunities and training  Track, maintain, and report monthly and quarterly operation metrics to direct supervisor  Continuously communicate with customer points of contact  Comply with internal policies/procedures to ensure SOC1 compliance and customer SLAs are met  Support new analysts during the onboarding period. This includes department specific training, customer training, systems training, and department workflow  Create reusable department templates & training/reference materials  Drive customer success  Create on-time, high quality project deliverables while managing expectations internally and externally  Execute, analyze, and maintain GTN data and calculations within the GTN software suite  Perform ongoing maintenance processes and communicate deficiencies through reporting mechanisms  Perform analysis and troubleshooting for customers  Anticipate and meet shifting customer needs, proactively elevating issues as required  Value and build relationships with customer IT, operations, and finance staff  Collaborate cross-functionally  Work closely with the GTN Advisory team to provide critical analysis of GTN-related data sets, and triage customer issues and reconciliation variances  Assist cross-functional business teams to meet goals of shared service arrangements  Attend customer, department, and company meetings     Qualifications    What you’ll need to thrive in this role:     Understanding of the GAAP principles related to revenue recognition and gross-to-net accounting practices  Knowledge of the pharma supply chain and contracting, and the relationship to data flows through GTN models – including but not limited to direct sales, chargebacks, rebates, and copay data.   Ability to demonstrate business analytical skills, a high accuracy rate, and attention to detail  Exhibit superior communication and influencing skills: oral, written, listening and presentation skills  Desire to continuously improve skills through continuing self-training, education, and personal development  Proactive with a pleasant manner; self-starter with a strong sense of ownership and responsibility  Ability to adhere to processes and controls to satisfy routine internal/ external audits     What you’ll bring to the table:      Exceptional Excel and PowerPoint skills  Minimum B.A. / B.S., CPA or MBA preferred with majors in Accounting, Finance, Economics, or similar  1-3 years of Life Sciences industry experience  Recommended 1-2 years of accounting experience working on the customer side or at a consultancy  Knowledge and/or user experience in the financial system is a plus (SAP, Oracle, Hyperion, forecast tools, etc.)    Additional Information   What does IntegriChain have to offer?     Mission driven: Work with the purpose of helping to improve patients' lives!   Excellent and affordable medical benefits + non-medical perks including Flexible Paid Time Off, 401(k) Plan with a Company Match to prepare for your future, Parental Leave, Student Loan Reimbursement and much more!  Robust Learning & Development opportunities including over 700+ development courses free to all employees.     IntegriChain is committed to equal treatment and opportunity in all aspects of recruitment, selection, and employment without regard to race, color, religion, national origin, ethnicity, age, sex, marital status, physical or mental disability, gender identity, sexual orientation, veteran or military status, or any other category protected under the law. IntegriChain is an equal opportunity employer; committed to creating a community of inclusion, and an environment free from discrimination, harassment, and retaliation.    Our policy on visa sponsorship for US based positions:   Applicants for employment in the US must have valid work authorization that does not now and/or will not in the future require sponsorship of a visa for employment authorization in the US by IntegriChain.  ",
