    "description": " Company Description   IntegriChain is the data and application backbone for market access departments of Life Sciences manufacturers. We deliver the data, the applications, and the business process infrastructure for patient access and therapy commercialization. More than 250 manufacturers rely on our ICyte Platform to orchestrate their commercial and government payer contracting, patient services, and distribution channels. ICyte is the first and only platform that unites the financial, operational, and commercial data sets required to support therapy access in the era of specialty and precision medicine. With ICyte, Life Sciences innovators can digitalize their market access operations, freeing up resources to focus on more data-driven decision support. With ICyte, Life Sciences innovators are digitalizing labor-intensive processes – freeing up their best talent to identify and resolve coverage and availability hurdles and to manage pricing and forecasting complexity.  We are headquartered in Philadelphia, PA (USA), with offices in: Ambler, PA (USA); Pune, India; and Medellín, Colombia. For more information, visit www.integrichain.com, or follow us on Twitter @IntegriChain and LinkedIn.   Job Description   The Consultant, is part of an elite team of consultants who leverage the Life Sciences domain expertise to analyze, model, and synthesize information to provide insight to our clients on matters related to GP, GTN, FMV, SPTR, and pricing and contracting matters. The ideal candidate will demonstrate high-level analytical thinking combined with the technical sophistication and marketing-savvy approach to each business scenario.  Responsibilities:    Assist clients with developing their government pricing methodology, performing calculations, and advising on strategic pricing related matters  Prepare, analyze, and submit monthly and quarterly product pricing information and other pertinent data to CMS and the Department of Veterans Affairs. This would include the calculation and reporting of Best Price, Average Manufacturer Price, Average Sale Price, Non-Federal Average Manufacturer Price and Public Health Service pricing for applicable client products  Perform Bona Fide Service Fee evaluations and Fair Market Value Analyses  Provide insights on GTN liabilities across government and commercial channels, including managed care contracts, Medicaid, Public Health Service (PHS) 340B, Tricare, returns, copay and Coverage Gap  Support clients with calculating their Branded Drug Fee estimates and on-going support  Perform true-ups based on actual versus accrued  Analyze, explain and meaningfully summarize government pricing variances  Support customers’ monthly close process, including establishing accruals, refreshing forecasts, providing critical analysis of data, and alerting customers to potential changes that may affect their business  Continuously communicate with the customer teams in order to stay on top of all developments relevant to future product development and performance  Create on-time, high quality project deliverables while managing expectations internally and externally  Demonstrate value to our customers and drive incremental opportunities  Contribute to FCS thought leadership and benchmarking capabilities through networking and collaboration with customers and colleagues, research, project delivery, and conference attendance     Qualifications     Bachelor's degree in a relevant field (Accounting, Science, Economics, Engineering, or Finance)  Understanding of Market Access and Healthcare delivery  Knowledge of the US pharma supply chain and contracting and government pricing  Experience as the customer-facing consulting lead for related projects  Strong interpersonal and communication skills  Highly proficient in Excel, Word and PowerPoint  Excellent understanding of cross-functional teamwork  Excellent presentation skills  2 - 5 years of accounting experience working in the life science industry, audit, and or consulting capacity    Additional Information   What does IntegriChain have to offer?     Mission driven: Work with the purpose of helping to improve patients' lives!   Excellent and affordable medical benefits + non-medical perks including Flexible Paid Time Off and much more!  Robust Learning & Development opportunities including over 700+ development courses free to all employees    IntegriChain is committed to equal treatment and opportunity in all aspects of recruitment, selection, and employment without regard to race, color, religion, national origin, ethnicity, age, sex, marital status, physical or mental disability, gender identity, sexual orientation, veteran or military status, or any other category protected under the law. IntegriChain is an equal opportunity employer; committed to creating a community of inclusion, and an environment free from discrimination, harassment, and retaliation.  ",
