er data exceptions queue  Effective and crisp communication with team leaders and internal stakeholders regarding data anomalies or the status of master data assignments.   Assist Data Management Office in tracking day-to-day activities     Qualifications    Qualifications and Competencies:     Bachelor's Degree  Knowledge or previous experience with data analysis tools such as Microsoft excel strongly preferred  Adept at internet research utilizing websites and web portals / databases  Eagerness to identify issues and accurately resolve data quality  Excellent verbal and written communication skills  Organized with an ability to prioritize and consistently follow-through  Flexible and Adaptable to feedback  Capable of working both autonomous and in a team  1+ years experience in a data analyst role with knowledge of master data maintenance preferred    Additional Information   What does IntegriChain have to offer?     Mission driven: Work with the purpose of helping to improve patients' lives!   Excellent and affordable medical benefits + non-medical perks including Flexible Paid Time Off  Robust Learning & Development opportunities including over 700+ development courses free to all employees    IntegriChain is committed to equal treatment and opportunity in all aspects of recruitment, selection, and employment without regard to race, color, religion, national origin, ethnicity, age, sex, marital status, physical or mental disability, gender identity, sexual orientation, veteran or military status, or any other category protected under the law. IntegriChain is an equal opportunity employer; committed to creating a community of inclusion, and an environment free from discrimination, harassment, and retaliation.  ",
