    "datePosted": "2025-04-10T02:51:02.000Z",
    "identifier": {
        "name": "IntegriChain",
        "@type": "PropertyValue",
        "value": "744000052987786"
    },
    "description": " Company Description   IntegriChain is the data and application backbone for market access departments of Life Sciences manufacturers. We deliver the data, the applications, and the business process infrastructure for patient access and therapy commercialization. More than 250 manufacturers rely on our ICyte Platform to orchestrate their commercial and government payer contracting, patient services, and distribution channels. ICyte is the first and only platform that unites the financial, operational, and commercial data sets required to support therapy access in the era of specialty and precision medicine. With ICyte, Life Sciences innovators can digitalize their market access operations, freeing up resources to focus on more data-driven decision support. With ICyte, Life Sciences innovators are digitalizing labor-intensive processes – freeing up their best talent to identify and resolve coverage and availability hurdles and to manage pricing and forecasting complexity.  We are headquartered in Philadelphia, PA (USA), with offices in: Ambler, PA (USA); Pune, India; and Medellín, Colombia. For more information, visit www.integrichain.com, or follow us on Twitter @IntegriChain and LinkedIn.  We are excited to offer a hybrid working environment for our employees. To be successful in this role, there are some requirements to visit our office locations from quarterly to a few times a quarter for workshops, team meetings and collaboration between teams. There may be potential for international travel annually or as needed based on business needs.   Description   Job Description   Mission:   The Government Pricing Senior Manager, within the Operational Consulting practice at IntegriChain, is part of an elite team of consultants who leverage their Life Sciences domain expertise to analyze, model, and synthesize secondary information to provide insights to our Government Pricing (GP) customers. The Senior Manager provides prompt, accurate, and compliant GP advice to our customers and provides strategic and compliance recommendations while building strong, trusted customer relationships.  The Senior Manager will partner with our customers - many of whom leverage IntegriChain’s services across Contracts & Pricing, Gross-to-Net, Channel and Patient – to ensure they understand the complex pricing, regulatory and compliance issues faced by manufacturers in the industry and more importantly, how these issues relate to each customer’s specific portfolio and business objectives. Collaboration with team members across departments, to ensure high level of customer experience, across all of the services IntegriChain offers to our customers will be a key expectation in this role.  This position requires crisp consulting skills: the daily demonstration of complex, analytical thinking and strategic recommendations. Leading by example, this individual will also teach and mentor team members to grow their expertise in these areas. Outside of ensuring high quality delivery and team development, this individual will support the sales process through the identification and scoping of new opportunities, collaborate with Consulting leaders in the development of new practice offerings and help drive resourcing decisions across the team. This individual will also be an empathetic leader who can foster collaboration and establish a positive team atmosphere in an increasing remote workplace. This candidate will command an expertise of Contracts and Pricing matters, win our customers’ trust, and drive growth at our customers. He or she will foster a team-wide customer-focused attitude and nurture our customer relationships to build long lasting partnerships.  The Senior Manager will be responsible for working with pre-commercial manufacturers bringing their first product to market. In these situations, the Senior Manager assists our customers in deploying a best in breed GP framework in order to support a successful product launch/commercialization. The Senior Manager will also be responsible for spearheading one-time projects, whether it is the development of a new one-time project opportunity or utilizing existing templates to deliver existing one-time projects to customers.  The ideal candidate will demonstrate high-level analytical and strategic thinking and possess the technical skillsets to deliver high quality work products, such as price impact scenario models and data analysis. The Senior Manager must be able to communicate complex concepts in a simple and clear manner via all modes of communication (e.g., reports, emails, PPT, in person and/or Zoom meetings).The Senior Manger must be able to lead and run well-structured meetings with C-Suite Executives, while continually keeping compliance at the forefront of our support.  This role requires the ability to lead customer accounts independently and provide high quality deliverables with very little oversight. This role also requires the individual to be inquisitive and to evaluate different scenarios in order to arrive at the right solution to the problem at hand.   Responsibilities:     Provide strategic, operational, and compliance advice relating to the various U.S. Government Programs, including Medicaid, FSS, 340B, and Medicare, as well as methodology guidance for the related GP calculations (e.g., AMP, BP, URA, ASP, PHS 340B, Non-FAMP and FCP)  Oversee Federal Supply Schedule contract compliance on behalf of IntegriChain’s customers, including contract maintenance, Public Law submissions, tracking customer monitoring, and negotiating contract changes with the VA  Assess customers’ current state GP processes, benchmark against industry norms and best practices, develop recommendations, and guide customers down the path to achieve these improvements  Lead pre-commercial customer engagements and ensure the successful and timely completion of all GP and other contracts and pricing pre-launch activities   Provide industry insights while also identifying key issues that may impact a customer’s business  Update and/or develop policies and procedure documentation for customers to ensure compliance with government regulations and effective corporate governance  Continually improve customer account satisfaction in order to encourage referrals, drive incremental revenue opportunities, and ensure renewal business on existing accounts  Create deliverables of the utmost quality for customers, manage expectations internally and externally, and provide on or ahead-of-time delivery  Establish immediate rapport and rapidly build trust with customers by providing decisive counsel and concise, accurate deliverables  Manage multiple projects in parallel, while ensuring timely delivery and responses to customer requests  Provide day-to-day people management of at least one (1) US-based team member including proper performance management, encouragement of professional development, focus on quality and process adherence, and an overall emphasis on team building and camaraderie; also includes skill development and helping to grow Advisory knowledge  Work within a rapidly growing organization where cross-functional communication is important and a willingness to evolve and adapt to changing organization needs and challenges is imperative  Understand the overall organization structure and interplay of the various segments within IntegriChain  Contribute to IntegriChain’s industry-leading thought leadership capabilities through networking and collaboration with customers and colleagues, independent and project-based research, project delivery, and conference attendance  Additional responsibilities as deemed necessary by Advisory leadership     Qualifications    Requirements     Minimum B.A. / B.S.   Minimum 7-10 years of consulting experience in the contracts and pricing arena within the pharma and biotech industry, with direct experience in Government Pricing and FSS contracting  Ability to respond to change or unexpected developments in a productive way while remaining a steady, calming influence for the team and customers.   Motivated to lead; accomplishment of daily activities proactively and independently  Experience as the customer-facing consulting lead for complex GP activities and deliverables – the ability to deeply describe all steps, approaches, pitfalls, and how to mitigate risk and achieve success  Strong interpersonal skills and understanding of cross-functional teamwork  Mastery of Excel and PowerPoint with excellent presentation skills  Excellent business analytical skills, a high accuracy rate, and attention to detail  Very strong understanding of government pricing practices, calculation methodologies, healthcare programs, and supporting regulations  Must be diplomatic, persuasive, and able to establish a good rapport with the full spectrum of internal and external partners, from operators to Sr. Executives  Must consistently demonstrate knowledge beyond the key subject areas and be recognized as a connector of key technical/subject information with larger business goals  Demonstrate problem-solving and decision-making skills with the ability to “think on his/her feet” and suggest alternatives and solutions  Exhibit superior communication and influencing skills including oral, written, listening, and presenting    Additional Information   What does IntegriChain have to offer?   Mission driven: Work with the purpose of helping to improve patients' lives!    Excellent and affordable medical benefits + non-medical perks including Student Loan Reimbursement, Flexible Paid Time Off and Paid Parental Leave  401(k) Plan with a Company Match to prepare for your future  Robust Learning & Development opportunities including over 700+ development courses free to all employees    IntegriChain is committed to equal treatment and opportunity in all aspects of recruitment, selection, and employment without regard to race, color, religion, national origin, ethnicity, age, sex, marital status, physical or mental disability, gender identity, sexual orientation, veteran or military status, or any other category protected under the law. IntegriChain is an equal opportunity employer; committed to creating a community of inclusion, and an environment free from discrimination, harassment, and retaliation.    Our policy on visa sponsorship for US based positions:   Applicants for employment in the US must have valid work authorization that does not now and/or will not in the future require sponsorship of a visa for employment authorization in the US by IntegriChain.  ",
