    "description": " Job Description   The Senior Government Pricing Analyst is a key member of IntegriChain’s Access Management Operations organization, which provides managed services and business process outsourcing in support of bio-pharmaceutical clients.   What This Role Entails   The Senior GP Analyst supports the data preparation, validation, calculation and analysis of price reporting required by the following government programs:Medicaid Drug Rebate  Medicare Part B  VA Federal Supply Schedule  PHS 340B Drug Discount  Prepares and validates underlying data for one or more of the following: Average Manufacturer Price (AMP), Best Price (BP), Average Sales Price (ASP), non-Federal Average Manufacturer Price (nFAMP), Federal Ceiling Price (FCP), Industrial Funding Fee (IFF) and Unit Rebate Amounts (URA).  Responsible for review and maintenance of key master data utilized within all Government Pricing calculations.  Manages the clients’ class of trade hierarchy and ensures that all incoming transactions are tagged or mapped to the correct designation.  Analyzes calculation results and identify the source of variances that are observed.  Works closely with clients, GP Manager and technical team to resolve system, data and process issues.  Documents all revisions and data manipulations on clients’ data as per financial controls and standard operating procedures.  Ensures timely and accurate calculation of assigned government prices based on the monthly, quarterly and annual schedule. SGPA will review calculations with Manager and obtain approval signoff (and execute any other required SOPs) before communicating prices to clients, the appropriate government agencies (CMS, VA/DOD, etc.) or internal Medicaid Rebates users.  Responsible for maintaining SOPs, SOX/SOC-1 documentation and price calculation evidence of work.",
