    "description": " Company Description   IntegriChain is the data and application backbone for market access departments of Life Sciences manufacturers. We deliver the data, the applications, and the business process infrastructure for patient access and therapy commercialization. More than 250 manufacturers rely on our ICyte Platform to orchestrate their commercial and government payer contracting, patient services, and distribution channels. ICyte is the first and only platform that unites the financial, operational, and commercial data sets required to support therapy access in the era of specialty and precision medicine. With ICyte, Life Sciences innovators can digitalize their market access operations, freeing up resources to focus on more data-driven decision support. With ICyte, Life Sciences innovators are digitalizing labor-intensive processes freeing up their best talent to identify and resolve coverage and availability hurdles and to manage pricing and forecasting complexity.  We are headquartered in Philadelphia, PA (USA), with offices in: Ambler, PA (USA); Pune, India; and Medelln, Colombia. For more information, visit www.integrichain.com, or follow us on Twitter @IntegriChain and LinkedIn.   Responsibilities     Design, develop, and deploy RPA solutions using UiPath to automate processes such as portal interactions, file downloads, and file manipulation.  Create and maintain development documentation, including workflow diagrams, process descriptions, and technical specifications.  Investigate and resolve root cause issues for automation failures or inefficiencies, ensuring robust and scalable solutions.  Perform initial happy path testing to ensure workflows meet functional requirements before formal testing begins.  Leverage SQL databases for data manipulation, integration, and storage to support automated processes.  Utilize UiPath ReFramework to build structured, scalable, and reusable automations.  Develop reusable libraries and components to optimize automation efforts.  Incorporate C# or VB.NET when needed to enhance automation capabilities.  Work with UiPath Orchestrator to test automations.  Collaborate with the project manager to gather and clarify automation requirements, provide regular status updates, and deliver tailored solutions.  Stay organized and effectively manage multiple tickets in a fast-paced, dynamic environment.  Maintain open and clear communication with team members.  Work independently while building and maintaining strong relationships with colleagues.  Contribute to a positive and collaborative work environment, actively participating in team meetings and initiatives.     Professional Approach     Ready to work in flexible working hours as per the need  Good communication skills (written, verbal, listening, and articulation)     Qualifications    Requirements      Bachelors degree in Computer Science, Information Technology, or a related field from a reputed institute.  UiPath Expertise:   Hands-on experience with UiPath Studio and Orchestrator is essential.  Deep understanding of UiPath ReFramework and its application in building scalable automations.  Proven experience in automating web-based processes and portals.  Ability to create reusable libraries and modules.   Programming Knowledge:   Experience with C# or VB.NET for extending automation functionality.  Familiarity with Python is a plus.   Database Skills:   Proficiency in using SQL for data manipulation, integration, and storage.   Testing and Debugging:   Experience in conducting happy path testing and addressing exceptions during development.  Strong troubleshooting skills to identify and resolve root cause issues in automations.   Soft Skills:   Excellent communication skills (written, verbal, and listening).  Strong organizational skills and ability to manage multiple tasks effectively.  Professional demeanor with a proactive approach to problem-solving and collaboration.   Work Ethic:   Willingness to extend working hours as per client requirements.  Ability to adapt to a fast-paced and dynamic environment while maintaining quality deliverables.     Additional Information   IntegriChain is committed to equal treatment and opportunity in all aspects of recruitment, selection, and employment without regard to race, color, religion, national origin, ethnicity, age, sex, marital status, physical or mental disability, gender identity, sexual orientation, veteran or military status, or any other category protected under the law. IntegriChain is an equal opportunity employer; committed to creating a community of inclusion, and an environment free from discrimination, harassment, and retaliation.  Locations - Pune, India  ",
