    "description": " Job Description   IntegriChain is seeking a detail-oriented and collaborative data steward with strong communication skills for our Patient Data Stewardship team. The team work as subject matter experts in the rapidly-developing patient data analytics space. Working on this team, candidates would develop and leverage knowledge to support pharmaceutical manufacturers by investigating and resolving data issues that obstruct or obscure the patient journey. They would also be contributing to the continued development of the team’s processes and tools, making use of new resources and techniques as they become available and areas for growth are identified.  This role requires an investigative mind, strong communication skills, and high attention to detail, as well as the ability to recognize and advance opportunities for improvement in existing processes. In addition, ideal candidates will be comfortable working with members of cross functional internal teams, external stakeholders, and specialty pharmacies to both support and improve existing programs.  Duties  Monitor and report on data processing for expected file receipt and incoming data quality  Conduct patient matching activities, including HIPAA Protected Health Information (PHI)  Access, manipulate, and analyze data using SQL, Power BI, MS Excel, and Python  Communicate with manufacturers, specialty pharmacies, and internal teams to efficiently resolve data quality issues  Record issues and manage ongoing initiatives via Jira and other tooling  Assist in the development of process enhancements and streamlining of existing standard operating procedures (SOPs)  Collaborate effectively with the other Patient Stewards to advance both short and long-term projects  Adhere to strict data governance controls around PHI",
