        "@type": "PropertyValue",
        "value": "7212_1066601314"
    },
    "description": " Company Description   IntegriChain helps pharmaceutical manufacturers bring their science to market, ensuring patients have affordable, timely, and sustainable access to therapy. We are doing this by building pharmaceuticals' data-driven commercialization platform, from strategy to operational execution.  IntegriChain is uniquely focused on connecting the commercial, financial, and operational dimensions of drug access and profitability. We've brought together technology, data, consulting, and outsourcing capabilities that span contracting and pricing, channel management, patient support, and gross-to-net finance.  We are headquartered in Philadelphia, PA (USA), with offices in Ambler, PA (USA), Pune, India, and Medelln, Colombia. For more information, visit www.integrichain.com or follow us on Twitter @IntegriChain and LinkedIn.   Job Description    Your mission at IntegriChain   The mission of this role is to ensure the quality of functional solution delivery to clients while building and maintaining overall client satisfaction. We are looking for a visionary functional lead to assist with the design and execution of complex solutions to support our customer needs.    Perform functional lead project roles  Assist in the design of solutions  Own client interaction, relationships, and onsite presence to support the functional solution delivery to the client  Ability to work autonomously and in independent work environment  Mentoring of junior project team members     What You'll Need To Thrive In This Role     Can lead/execute a project workstream with limited day-to-day supervision  Gather requirements for and design complex solutions to provide business goals  Support project plans, status reports, and other project documentation  Oversees development of engagement deliverables  Provides functional thought leadership internally and to clients  Provides effective communication with internal and clients  Initiates/leads internal projects   Mentors Analysts, Senior Analysts, and Lead Analysts  Participates in the recruiting process as appropriate  Participates in business development activities  Demonstrates higher levels of operating autonomy - able to perform tasks related to the execution of a client engagement without day-to-day supervision; knows appropriate times to seek assistance and review of work products  Supports sales opportunities and estimates development  Tracks assigned tasks to project work  Understands the \"big picture\" of what needs to be accomplished and raises concerns/issues in a timely fashion  Understand the primary financial drivers of the business and engagement financials  Mentors Analysts and Senior Analysts  Has consulting experience or relevant industry experience  Willingness to travel     Qualifications    What you'll bring to the table:     At least 3 years of systems implementation/upgrade experience spanning the software development lifecycle (requirements, design, build, test, implement)   At least 3 years experience in Pharmaceutical commercial contracting (chargebacks, purchase based rebates, utilization based rebates)  Experience with Model N Flex or Model N Powered by N strongly preferred  Cross functional experience in pharmaceutical Medicaid and Government Pricing a huge plus  Mentoring of junior project team members  Has mastered the requirements of Senior Analyst  Demonstrates higher levels of operating autonomy - able to perform tasks related to the execution of a client engagement without day-to-day supervision; knows appropriate times to seek assistance and review of work products  Supports sales opportunities and estimate development  Tracks assigned tasks to project work  Understands the \"big picture\" of what needs to be accomplished and raises concerns/issues in timely fashion  Understand the basic financial drivers of the business and engagement financials  Mentors Analysts and Senior Analysts  Has consulting experience or relevant industry experience  Willingness to travel     Additional Information    What does IntegriChain have to offer?     Mission driven: Work with the purpose of helping to improve patients' lives!   Excellent and affordable medical benefits + non-medical perks including Flexible Paid Time Off, 401(k) Plan with a Company Match to prepare for your future, Parental Leave, Student Loan Reimbursement and much more!  Robust Learning & Development opportunities including over 700+ development courses free to all employees.    IntegriChain is committed to equal treatment and opportunity in all aspects of recruitment, selection, and employment without regard to race, color, religion, national origin, ethnicity, age, sex, marital status, physical or mental disability, gender identity, sexual orientation, veteran or military status, or any other category protected under the law. IntegriChain is an equal opportunity employer; committed to creating a community of inclusion, and an environment free from discrimination, harassment, and retaliation.   Our policy on visa sponsorship for US based positions:  Applicants for employment in the US must have valid work authorization that does not now and/or will not in the future require sponsorship of a visa for employment authorization in the US by IntegriChain.   Videos To Watch   https://youtu.be/2Q_ODlJxDcQ?feature=shared   Required   Preferred  Job Industries    Other    ",
