    "description": "Vibracoustic is part of the Freudenberg Group. The company ensures a smooth and quiet ride experience in every vehicle. We are driven by our purpose of adding comfort to mobility and providing the perfect solution for the NVH challenges of our automotive customers. As a leading supplier, Vibracoustic is the right place for open-minded, ambitious team-players with a hands-on mentality. Our innovative, safe and dynamic working atmosphere offers many opportunities for your personal growth and development in a global network. Want to join the team?   Morganfield, KY  On-Site   Vibracoustic USA Inc.  You support our team as    Quality Engineer     Responsibilities      Supervises plant quality functions; coordinates APQP functions. Participates in APQP meetings and coordinates the review of the Production Tooling Progress Report.  Creates / assists in implementing and maintaining control plans, work/inspection instructions, local procedures, visual aids/samples.  Prepares sample submissions for PPAP Packages; supervises the retention of PPAP samples.  Assists in maintaining IATF-16949 certification and meeting customer quality requirements.  Designs, implements and maintains various programs to continually improve quality processes within the facility.  Communicate with customers through their internal systems. Pro-active and customer initiated plant visits.  Acts as Quality Department liaison with the supplier to investigate quality problems and as a resource to the supplier pertaining to product quality.  Develops and implements corrective actions (8-D) for internal quality and delivery problems.   Applies statistical analysis and concepts to the manufacturing process.  Complete dimensional layouts using lab equipment, as necessary.  Works with the Assembly Lead to oversee the Firewall/Reinspect area. Ensure I- charts on boards weekly.  Assists in making dimensional and/or mechanical inspection and test of assemblies and sub-assemblies to ensure conformance with quality standards.  Create programs and operate CMM. Mount, install, align and secure tools attachments fixtures and work pieces on CMM machine using hand tools and/or precision measuring instruments.     Qualifications      Bachelor's Degree (B.S. or B.A.) from four year college or university in appropriate technical field. One to three years of related experience and/or training; or equivalent combination of education and experience.  Desired: Basic S.P.C., measurement systems, Basic Metrology, Geometric Dimensioning & Tolerancing  Continuous Improvement training, Blue print reading, and gage calibration also a plus.     Some of your Benefits     401K Match:  Save for retirement with the company's help.   Health Insurance:  Rely on comprehensive services whenever you need it.   Vacation:  We offer time off to refresh and recharge.   Paid Holidays:  With paid-time off, local holidays are all the way more relaxing.   Education Reimbursement:  Receive financial aid to help propel your career to the next level.  Click here to go directly to our career page. Drive your career!  The Freudenberg Group is an equal opportunity employer that is committed to diversity and inclusion. Employment opportunities are available to all applicants and associates without regard to race, color, religion, creed, gender (including pregnancy, childbirth, breastfeeding, or related medical conditions), gender identity or expression, national origin, ancestry, age, mental or physical disability, genetic information, marital status, familial status, sexual orientation, protected military or veteran status, or any other characteristic protected by applicable law.",
