    "description": "Vibracoustic is part of the Freudenberg Group. The company ensures a smooth and quiet ride experience in every vehicle. We are driven by our purpose of adding comfort to mobility and providing the perfect solution for the NVH challenges of our automotive customers. As a leading supplier, Vibracoustic is the right place for open-minded, ambitious team-players with a hands-on mentality. Our innovative, safe and dynamic working atmosphere offers many opportunities for your personal growth and development in a global network. Want to join the team?   Weinheim  Farmington Hills, MI  Hybrid Work   Vibracoustic SE & Co. KG  You support our team as   Director IT Corporate Functions And Financials (f/m/d)    Responsibilities      Strategic Alignment: You act as a proactive leader within the business, defining, changing and aligning IT architecture and strategy with reflect to corporate goals  Business Relationship Management: Ensuring alignment with business demands, you oversee the management of business relationships and service portfolios  Budget Leadership: Driving financial efficiency and operational excellence, you manage the overall IT budget in your value area  Team Leadership: You lead and develop a high-performance team of approx. 5 colleagues (located in Germany and India) to establish a sustainable organizational structure  Operational Excellence: You streamline IT services within your value area to achieve IT operational excellence  IT Service Management: You define and implement IT services within your value area “Corporate Functions and Financials”, ensuring alignment with the business goals     Qualifications      Leadership: As a proactive leadership within the business, you act as an internal thought leader and problem solver to drive change in IT and enable transformation within the business  Technical Expertise: You are proficient within Digital Core Applications, Business and Corporate Processes for Automotive Suppliers, as well as Integration Services, Business Analytics Systems and IT Service Management (ITIL)  Educational Background: You own a university degree in IT or an equivalent combination of education and experience  Experience: You have collected 8+ years in IT with in-depth knowledge of business models and strategies in Finance, Accounting, Controlling, HR, and Digital Business Processes  Project Management: You bring strong expertise in Project Management and IT Application Portfolio Management (LeanIX), as well as IT Demand Management Systems (ServiceNow)  Cultural Sensitivity and Language Skills: You combine intercultural openness, sensitivity, and respect with strong in- and external communication skills in English language (an additional major language is welcome)     Some of your Benefits     Performance Related Bonus:  When you have an impact, you can reap the rewards.   Flexible Work Models:  We allow for flexible work models to ensure both professional and personal success.   Safe Environment:  We strive to ensure safety remains a top priority, and provide a stable environment for our employees.   International Opportunities:  Grow in your career through international exchange and global job opportunities.   On-site Medical Service:  Our on-site medical service can handle a variety of medical needs.  Click here to go directly to our career page. Drive your career!  The Freudenberg Group is an equal opportunity employer that is committed to diversity and inclusion. Employment opportunities are available to all applicants and associates without regard to race, color, religion, creed, gender (including pregnancy, childbirth, breastfeeding, or related medical conditions), gender identity or expression, national origin, ancestry, age, mental or physical disability, genetic information, marital status, familial status, sexual orientation, protected military or veteran status, or any other characteristic protected by applicable law.",
