    "description": "Vibracoustic is part of the Freudenberg Group. The company ensures a smooth and quiet ride experience in every vehicle. We are driven by our purpose of adding comfort to mobility and providing the perfect solution for the NVH challenges of our automotive customers. As a leading supplier, Vibracoustic is the right place for open-minded, ambitious team-players with a hands-on mentality. Our innovative, safe and dynamic working atmosphere offers many opportunities for your personal growth and development in a global network. Want to join the team?   Morganfield, KY  On-Site   Vibracoustic USA Inc.  You support our team as    Maintenance Tech     Responsibilities      Maintenance Technician Level 1  Perform assigned daily inspections, preventive maintenance and safety checks of all machines and equipment defined in the maintenance operational system and listing of Key Equipment.  Fabrication and welding of items necessary for equipment installation and maintenance.  Utilize skills and knowledge to evaluate repair issues with mechanical, electrical, pneumatic and hydraulic systems of the machines.  Installation of utilities to machines (electrical, pneumatic and cooling water)  Document preventive maintenance to CMM software (PMC) and corrective maintenance activities in the maintenance log book.  Maintenance Technician Level 2  In addition to the requirements of Level 1 Technician the Level 2 Technician will:  Perform midlevel programming and adjustment of PLC’s, robots and Vision inspection systems.  Interpret specifications, read schematics and manuals to determine corrective measures required for proper maintenance and repair.  Maintenance Technician Level 3  In addition to the requirements of Level 1 and 2 Technician, the Level 3 Technician will:  Perform advanced programming and adjustment of PLC’s, robots and Vision inspection systems.  Assist maintenance supervisor in spare parts inventory control through utilization of the CMM software system (PMC)  Utilize supervisory skills to manage sub projects in the Maintenance Department  Provide support and training to Level 1 and Level 2 Maintenance Technicians  All Maintenance Technicians will  Assist in activities related to safety and will be an active member of the facilities safety team on their shift.  Have specific duties assigned to perform in an emergency situation.  Understand proper usage and disposal of all hazardous substances used in the facility  Understand the hazards and necessary PPE to utilize in their assigned tasks.     Qualifications      Vocational training in Industrial Maintenance.   Related experience with mechanical and electrical systems and controls.   Electrical, pneumatic and mechanical systems.   Programming PLC’s, HMI’s and robotic systems.   Specific training relative to the equipment utilized at this facility.     Some of your Benefits     Vacation:  We offer time off to refresh and recharge.   Paid Holidays:  With paid-time off, local holidays are all the way more relaxing.   401K Match:  Save for retirement with the company's help.   Health Insurance:  Rely on comprehensive services whenever you need it.   Education Reimbursement:  Receive financial aid to help propel your career to the next level.  Click here to go directly to our career page. Drive your career!  The Freudenberg Group is an equal opportunity employer that is committed to diversity and inclusion. Employment opportunities are available to all applicants and associates without regard to race, color, religion, creed, gender (including pregnancy, childbirth, breastfeeding, or related medical conditions), gender identity or expression, national origin, ancestry, age, mental or physical disability, genetic information, marital status, familial status, sexual orientation, protected military or veteran status, or any other characteristic protected by applicable law.",
