    "description": "Vibracoustic is part of the Freudenberg Group. The company ensures a smooth and quiet ride experience in every vehicle. We are driven by our purpose of adding comfort to mobility and providing the perfect solution for the NVH challenges of our automotive customers. As a leading supplier, Vibracoustic is the right place for open-minded, ambitious team-players with a hands-on mentality. Our innovative, safe and dynamic working atmosphere offers many opportunities for your personal growth and development in a global network. Want to join the team?   Queretaro  On-Site   Vibracoustic de México S.A. de C.V.  You support our team as    Master Production Scheduler (f/m/d)     Responsibilities      Responsible to lead on daily basis the CRITICOS meeting and plan production revision, requesting all necessary changes base on customer demand  Responsible to monitoring mold / model changes according production plan  Responsible to monitoring shipping plan base on customer demand  Responsible to schedule engineering samples and nonproductive material (production, packaging shipping)  Responsible to coordinate and track activities assigned to Logistics department for new projects / launch management  Responsible to alert to materials planner about shortages detected on daily basis production plan review and request contingency plan  Responsible to validate capacity constrain and alert to the plant in case is exceeded by customer demand     Qualifications      Degree in logistics administration, international trade, industrial or engineering career   3 years managing accounts of OEMs (Ford, Chrysler, GM) as customer service  Customer Plataforms  SAP  ASN,  Import-Export,  CTPAT,     Some of your Benefits     Cafeteria/ Canteen:  We offer fresh food on-site, both hot and cold.   Diversity & Inclusion:  We focus on providing an inclusive environment and recognize our diversity contributes to our success.   Corporate Events:  We celebrate success as a team, because only together can we achieve our goals.   On-site Medical Service:  Our on-site medical service can handle a variety of medical needs.   Safe Environment:  We strive to ensure safety remains a top priority, and provide a stable environment for our employees.  Click here to go directly to our career page. Drive your career!  The Freudenberg Group is an equal opportunity employer that is committed to diversity and inclusion. Employment opportunities are available to all applicants and associates without regard to race, color, religion, creed, gender (including pregnancy, childbirth, breastfeeding, or related medical conditions), gender identity or expression, national origin, ancestry, age, mental or physical disability, genetic information, marital status, familial status, sexual orientation, protected military or veteran status, or any other characteristic protected by applicable law.",
