    "description": "Vibracoustic is part of the Freudenberg Group. The company ensures a smooth and quiet ride experience in every vehicle. We are driven by our purpose of adding comfort to mobility and providing the perfect solution for the NVH challenges of our automotive customers. As a leading supplier, Vibracoustic is the right place for open-minded, ambitious team-players with a hands-on mentality. Our innovative, safe and dynamic working atmosphere offers many opportunities for your personal growth and development in a global network. Want to join the team?   Wuxi  On-Site   Vibracoustic (Wuxi) Vibration Isolators Co. Ltd.  You support our team as    Senior Application Engineer, Business Unit Mounts     Responsibilities      You realize the acquisition of target projects in cooperation with Sales  You manage global projects with high complexity over the entire lifecycle assuring profitability  You are fully responsible for project results in terms of quality, cost, and timing  To ensure customer satisfaction and to enable sustainable growth, you establish as a key contact for relevant technical functions at the customer  You ensure effective communication within the project team, and you execute internal as well as external project reviews  You interact professionally with the Top Management regularly providing management summaries     Qualifications      You hold a degree in Engineering or another technical subject  You have experience in project management and application engineering, ideally in the automotive industry  As an assertive team player with strong technical background you closely collaborate with product and process development  Based on your analytical thinking you translate customer needs into best product solutions  Strong communications skill enable you to communicate on eye level with different target groups from management to technical expert  Fluent English skills to collaborate with your international team colleagues complete your profile     Some of your Benefits     Diversity & Inclusion:  We focus on providing an inclusive environment and recognize our diversity contributes to our success.   Corporate Events:  We celebrate success as a team, because only together can we achieve our goals.   Flexible Work Models:  We allow for flexible work models to ensure both professional and personal success.   Welcome to career changers:  We look forward to your application, even if you do not have specific prior experience. All you need is the willingness to grow and develop   Personal Development:  We offer a variety of trainings to ensure you can develop in your career.  Click here to go directly to our career page. Drive your career!  The Freudenberg Group is an equal opportunity employer that is committed to diversity and inclusion. Employment opportunities are available to all applicants and associates without regard to race, color, religion, creed, gender (including pregnancy, childbirth, breastfeeding, or related medical conditions), gender identity or expression, national origin, ancestry, age, mental or physical disability, genetic information, marital status, familial status, sexual orientation, protected military or veteran status, or any other characteristic protected by applicable law.",
