    "description": "Vibracoustic is part of the Freudenberg Group. The company ensures a smooth and quiet ride experience in every vehicle. We are driven by our purpose of adding comfort to mobility and providing the perfect solution for the NVH challenges of our automotive customers. As a leading supplier, Vibracoustic is the right place for open-minded, ambitious team-players with a hands-on mentality. Our innovative, safe and dynamic working atmosphere offers many opportunities for your personal growth and development in a global network. Want to join the team?   Morganfield, KY  Evansville, IN  On-Site   Vibracoustic USA Inc.  You support our team as    Production Manager     Responsibilities      Diligently maintains a safe working environment for all employees, contractors, and guests.  Coordinates production activities with all departments in the plant to obtain optimum production and utilization of human resources, machines, and equipment.  Directly supervises and mentors production supervisors.  Reviews and analyzes production, quality, and operational reports to insure plant KPI’s are being met; and implements correct actions accordingly  Manages and actively seeks to reduce all forms of waste and cost related to production  Assures conformance with IATF 16949, ISO 14001, and HSE requirements.  Works with the materials department to plan production schedules and forecast labor needs  Assists the HR department in all personnel issues related to production employees including hiring, evaluation, promotion, conflict resolution, and when required, reprimands or termination.     Qualifications      Bachelor’s degree in an applicable field or applicable on-the-job training  Three or more years of experience in manufacturing operations  Proficient in Microsoft office products  Excellent verbal and written communication skills  On site: There is no remote or hybrid option available for this role.     Some of your Benefits     Health Insurance:  Rely on comprehensive services whenever you need it.   Vacation:  We offer time off to refresh and recharge.   401K Match:  Save for retirement with the company's help.   Paid Holidays:  With paid-time off, local holidays are all the way more relaxing.   Employee discounts:  Opportunities for deals on products and services.  Click here to go directly to our career page. Drive your career!  The Freudenberg Group is an equal opportunity employer that is committed to diversity and inclusion. Employment opportunities are available to all applicants and associates without regard to race, color, religion, creed, gender (including pregnancy, childbirth, breastfeeding, or related medical conditions), gender identity or expression, national origin, ancestry, age, mental or physical disability, genetic information, marital status, familial status, sexual orientation, protected military or veteran status, or any other characteristic protected by applicable law.",
