 Team.  Assure qualification, know-how transfer, check of sustainability and identification of improvement potentials within Plant Process Reviews and plant user trainings.  Support and coordinate in interface projects with Sales, SCM and IT.  Test and approve logistics changes in SAP / other ERP if necessary.  Process documentation.  Support of Logistics Management.     Qualifications      Academical degree with main focus on logistics or production.  Project & process management in the area of logistics processes.  Management experiences and leadership within projects.  Min. 5 years of experience in same or similar positions in the automotive industry.  Project & Process Management leading complex projects and international teams in the automotive industry.  Lean Experience.  Knowledge of SAP/ERP system.  Knowledge in logistics and production flows, warehouse and material flow planning.  Consulting and customizing experience in SAP processes (modules MM, WM, PP, SD, PM).  Very good written and spoken English skills, further languages are desirable.  Analytical thinking, eager to improve, able to organize and prioritize work / organization, leadership, contact and communications skills, customer oriented behavior, data preparation and analysis.   Enjoy business travel.  Strong cross-cultural skills.  Working independently.     Some of your Benefits     Corporate Events:  We celebrate success as a team, because only together can we achieve our goals.   Vacation:  We offer time off to refresh and recharge.   Paid Holidays:  With paid-time off, local holidays are all the way more relaxing.   Diversity & Inclusion:  We focus on providing an inclusive environment and recognize our diversity contributes to our success.   Personal Development:  We offer a variety of trainings to ensure you can develop in your career.  Click here to go directly to our career page. Drive your career!  The Freudenberg Group is an equal opportunity employer that is committed to diversity and 