    "description": "Vibracoustic is part of the Freudenberg Group. The company ensures a smooth and quiet ride experience in every vehicle. We are driven by our purpose of adding comfort to mobility and providing the perfect solution for the NVH challenges of our automotive customers. As a leading supplier, Vibracoustic is the right place for open-minded, ambitious team-players with a hands-on mentality. Our innovative, safe and dynamic working atmosphere offers many opportunities for your personal growth and development in a global network. Want to join the team?   Wuxi  On-Site   Vibracoustic (Wuxi) Vibration Isolators Co. Ltd.  You support our team as    Design Engineer, BUAS     Responsibilities      Development of BU-specific components based on the specifications in close collaboration with the application engineer, taking into account customer requirements as well as internal and legal requirements  Concept development, construction (3D/2D), strength calculations based on standards  Planning tests based on standards together with the application engineer  Necessary coordination with suppliers, process engineers and quality assurance, as well as other roles to ensure a robust and cost-efficient design  Responsible for an expert topic to be defined for standardization and its continuous improvement  Coordination of tasks in the extended team  Support FMEA  Support methods to improve workflows and products     Qualifications      Engineering degree (Master, Bachelor or Diploma in Mechanical, Industrial Engineering, Design Engineering or similar)  >3 years related work experience preferable  Specialized knowledge  CAD (CATIA, 3D/2D); Strength calculations with FEM, time management, presentation techniques  English fluently  Communicative, solution-oriented, responsible     Some of your Benefits     Cafeteria/ Canteen:  We offer fresh food on-site, both hot and cold.   Diversity & Inclusion:  We focus on providing an inclusive environment and recognize our diversity contributes to our success.   Personal Development:  We offer a variety of trainings to ensure you can develop in your career.   Safe Environment:  We strive to ensure safety remains a top priority, and provide a stable environment for our employees.   Vacation:  We offer time off to refresh and recharge.  Click here to go directly to our career page. Drive your career!  The Freudenberg Group is an equal opportunity employer that is committed to diversity and inclusion. Employment opportunities are available to all applicants and associates without regard to race, color, religion, creed, gender (including pregnancy, childbirth, breastfeeding, or related medical conditions), gender identity or expression, national origin, ancestry, age, mental or physical disability, genetic information, marital status, familial status, sexual orientation, protected military or veteran status, or any other characteristic protected by applicable law.",
